In article <phrCKHK2o.AL4@netcom.com> phr@netcom.com "Paul Rubin" writes:
>
> According to "The Ultra Secret", the Polish and British cryptanalysis
> of Enigma led Winterbotham to get the British to use one-time pads.

This seems plausible for command lines, but I sincerely doubt OTPs were
used in the field for tactical comms.  ("Code Breakers - Inside Story of
Bletchley Park", Ed. Hinsley & Stripp, describes several Axis codes used
by tactical units, eg using Playfair derivatives).


